## Additional Context for Families

**Critical distinction from other programs:** SLMB and QI-1 are **premium-only programs**[7]. If your loved one needs help with deductibles, co-insurance, or other cost-sharing, they may qualify for the **Qualified Medicare Beneficiary (QMB) program** instead, which has lower income limits ($1,235/month single, $1,663/month married[2]) but covers all cost-sharing plus premiums[2].

**Dual-eligible pathway:** If your loved one qualifies for SLMB *and* full Medicaid, they should ask about **SLMB Plus**, which provides additional benefits beyond premium payment[3].

**Application strategy:** Start by calling your State Health Insurance Assistance Program (SHIP) at 1-877-839-2675[3]. SHIP counselors can determine eligibility and help file the application at no cost. This is often easier than navigating the application alone.

**Income counting:** Social Security benefits, wages, pensions, and investment income all count, but certain exclusions apply[3]. If your loved one is close to the income limit, ask specifically about what income is excluded — you may still qualify.

